{# EXAMPLE: Anatomical Structure Localization #}
{# Supports single or multiple images. Requires at least one image. #}

**TASK:**

{% if target_structure %}
Localize the following anatomical structure: **{{ target_structure }}**
{% else %}
Localize the major anatomical structures visible in {% if images and images|length > 1 %}these images{% else %}this image{% endif %}.
{% endif %}

For each structure:
1. Identify and name the structure
2. Provide a bounding box in normalized coordinates [x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max]
3. Describe its appearance (size, shape, symmetry if applicable)
4. Note if the structure appears normal or abnormal
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
5. Specify which image the structure appears in
{% endif %}

{% if images and images|length > 0 %}
**IMAGES:**
{% for img in images %}
- {% if img.label %}{{ img.label }}{% else %}Image {{ loop.index }}{% endif %}: {{ img.width }}x{{ img.height }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

**OUTPUT FORMAT:**

```json
{
  "structures": [
    {
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
      "image_index": 0,
      "image_label": "string",
{% endif %}
      "name": "string (anatomical structure name)",
      "bbox": [x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max],
      "laterality": "left/right/midline/bilateral",
      "appearance": "normal/abnormal",
      "description": "string (morphological description)",
      "confidence": 0.0-1.0
    }
  ],
  "not_visible": ["list of expected structures not visualized"],
  "reasoning": "string (approach to structure identification)",
  "continue": true/false
}
```

**LOCALIZATION GUIDELINES:**

- Bounding boxes use normalized coordinates (0.0-1.0) relative to image dimensions
- For paired structures (e.g., lateral ventricles), localize each side separately
- Note asymmetries between bilateral structures
- If a target structure is not visible, explain why (e.g., not in imaging plane, obscured)
- Use standardized anatomical terminology
{% if images and images|length > 1 %}
- Track structures across multiple images when possible
- Note if the same structure appears differently in different sequences/views
{% endif %}

**COMMON STRUCTURES BY REGION:**

Brain: ventricles, basal ganglia, thalamus, brainstem, cerebellum, corpus callosum
Chest: heart, lungs, mediastinum, diaphragm, major vessels
Abdomen: liver, spleen, kidneys, pancreas, bowel, major vessels
